hire, England, United Kingdom","Lamport, Northamptonshire, England":"Lamport, Northamptonshire, England","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Vylles","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Carlos, Jesus, Manuel, Luis, Juan, Raul, Francisco, Julio, Alfonso, Javier, Roberto.","Catalan (<b>Vallès</b>): habitational name from a region of Catalonia named with <i>vallès</i> ‘of or relating to the valley’ (from Latin <i>vallensis</i>, an adjectival derivative of <i>vallis</i> ‘valley’).","Spanish: habitational name from any of the places called (Los) Valles, from <i>valles</i>, plural of <i>valle</i> ‘valley’."],"variants":[{"name":"Vallez","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Emilio, Adelaida, Francisco, Gregorio, Gustavo, Jaime, Juan, Luis, Manuel, Mario, Pablo, Raul.","Spanish (also <b>Vállez</b>): altered form of Spanish   Valles   or Catalan <b>Vallès</b>, influenced by the Spanish patronymic suffix <i>-ez</i>.","French (Nord): regional variant of   Vallet  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705206,"age":1,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":15,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":50,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705213,"age":72,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705216,"age":118,"year":"1688","toYear":"1689","julianDay":2337590,"title":"Glorious Revolution","description":"The Glorious Revolution brought the downfall of Catholic King James II and the reign of his Protestant daughter Mary and her Dutch husband, William III of Orange.","url":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/civil_war_revolution/glorious_revolution_01.shtml","urlTitle":"BBC - Glorious Revolution","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Vylles was born in 1570, in Lamport, Northamptonshire, England, his father, Thomas Viall, was 40 and his mother, Elizabeth, was 40. He married Elizabeth Litchfield in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parent